{
 "name": "RPlog_Blurred_Visions",
 "title": "Blurred Visions",
 "summary": "Crossing the decaying Yan Square on Dreven, the Falleen spymaster Ssanyu is accosted by a half-blind beggar crone called Auntie Maya, who recognizes her by name and insists she can see her. Maya draws Ssanyu into her squalid hovel and delivers a torrent of cryptic prophecy about a wrathful 'Dark One,' the return of the 'Cold Kings,' and a coming storm, urging Ssanyu to seek council with the Red Man and warning of disappointment, vengeance, and old wounds reopening. Ssanyu, coldly analytical, probes the visions and turns aside Maya's parables, but grows dangerously alarmed when the crone nearly shouts a forbidden name aloud. When Maya descends into uncontrollable, screeching chanting that risks exposing them both, Ssanyu draws a concealed neurolash and stuns the old woman into bloodied silence before slipping out of the hovel and closing the door behind her.",
